race.comment: JARRITO (9) sharp bred filly resuming. Never looked comfortable on the soft surface on debut when third over 1100m at Warwick Farm last June. Clearly come back a much stronger type judging by her two slick trial wins. The one to catch from the good gate. KILBRANNAN (5) resumes after coming out of some strong rating contests in his first campaign. Both trials at Warwick Farm had merit and is sure to be thereabouts from the inside gate. Top three player. ADMIRE ME (6) Admire Mars filly from Magna Amica on debut for the Brad Widdup stable. The four good trials should have her forward enough for this. Leading prospect. I AM CARROT (2) back for his second campaign and gelded over the break. No match at Listed grade when seventh in the Phoenix over 1500m at Eagle Farm on June 7. Fitted with the two trials and the lugging bit goes on. Can surprise fresh.
